Hochtief Posts First-Quarter Loss, Cuts 2011 Forecast

-- B y   M a r i a j o s e   V e r a
-- 
2011-05-16T05:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/hochtief-posts-first-quarter-loss-cuts-2011-forecast.html
Hochtief AG (HOT)  posted a loss of 169.5
million euros in the first quarter after a profit of 34.1
million euros in the year-ago period. This was due to an
“earnings collapse” at its Asia-Pacific unit Leighton Holdings
Ltd., the company said in an e-mailed statement. Hochtief cut
its forecast for 2011 and confirmed its guidance for 2012 and
2013.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mariajose Vera in Munich at 
 mvera1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at   acullen8@bloomberg.net . 